Package com.fxgraph.graph

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICell
    Interface that any graph cell must implement.
    IEdge
    Interface that any graph edge must implement.
    IGraphNode
    An interface that anything must implement in order to be displayed in a Graph.
    SequenceDiagram.IActorCell
    Interface that any sequence diagram actor cell must implement.
    SequenceDiagram.IMessageEdge
    An edge representing a sequence diagram message between actors.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Arrow
    A straight arrow, composed of a main line and a fin line connected to either side of the end point.
    CartesianGraph
    A specialized graph that plots data in the Cartesian x,y plane.
    Graph
    Encapsulates a 2d graph model (graph nodes: cells, edges) and its presentation onto a specialized javafx pane.
    Model
    Owns all cells and edges that can be displayed on a graph.
    MultiplotModel
    A model containing cells and edges in a manner specialized for storing multiple datasets/plots of 2d coordinate points (cells) and their connections (edges).
    NodeGestures
    Handles interaction with graph nodes, so far only including mouse dragging for translation.
    NodeGestures.DragContext
    Stores x,y anchor/start point information for a graph node drag in progress.
    PannableCanvas
    A specialized pane that displays graphics children in a dynamic viewport.
    PannableCanvas.DragContext
    Mouse drag context used for scene and nodes.
    SequenceDiagram
    A specialized graph that represents a sequence diagram.
    SequenceDiagram.ActorCell
    A specialized cell representing an actor in a sequence diagram.
    ViewportGestures
    Listeners for making the scene's viewport draggable and zoomable.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CartesianGraph.PlotMode
    CartesianGraph plot modes.
